# Festag — auth long-text info tip

When an **under-title** auth field (Dev username „Benutzer eingeben“, workspace name while editing, similar hero inputs) becomes **too long** for the compact 32px line:

## Behavior

1. Keep **typing in the compact field** — never move focus into a second edit surface.
2. Show a **small info tip below** the field with the full name (read-only).
3. Tip is **borderless** (soft shadow only) — no stroke/hairline.
4. Close on: **click outside**, **Escape**, **blur** away from the field, or when the value fits again.
5. Close **smoothly** (opacity fade) — do not vanish instantly on mouseover of nearby chrome.
6. After close: the compact field keeps ellipsis; focusing the truncated field again reopens the tip if still overflowing.

## Implementation

- Reuse `components/auth/AuthExpandableTextField.tsx` — do not invent a one-off per page.
- Overflow detection: `input.scrollWidth > input.clientWidth` on the compact field.
- Portal tip to `document.body` with `position: fixed` under the field (`field.bottom + 10`).
- Match Festag dark/light popup tokens (`--festag-black-popup`), Aeonik, calm motion.

## Do not

- Open an editable duplicate input over/on top of the field.
- Put the tip directly in front of / overlapping the input.
- Use a stroked border on the tip.
- Force a full-screen modal for this.

## DE / EN

**DE:** Zu langer Benutzer-/Workspace-Name unter dem Titel → kleines Info-Tooltip darunter mit dem vollen Namen; Tippen bleibt im Feld; Schließen per Klick außerhalb / Esc, smooth.

**EN:** Overlong under-title username/workspace → small info tip below with full name; typing stays in the field; dismiss via outside click / Esc, smooth fade.
